<title type="html"><![CDATA[Repairing front-loading NES console cartridge slot]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7769&amp;p=78442#p78442"><![CDATA[
I also bought a front-loading NES in a bundle (refurbished with a new 72-pin, can't push down), the seller gave me some games that she said were "broken". It would never work as much as a tried on the one she gave me, but it worked right away on my top-loader NES. On my old regular NES that I had as a kid there were some games that took forever to get working (Zelda 2 was particularly bad).<br /><br />Basically, if you mess with them enough and clean the contacts you will eventually get the game working, but it will never work nearly as well as your top-loader. But definitely cut off the CIC as it's annoyingly picky.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4219">nothingnew</a> — Sat May 21, 2011 2:05 pm</p><hr />
