<title type="html"><![CDATA[Repairing front-loading NES console cartridge slot]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7769&amp;p=78426#p78426"><![CDATA[
The "replacement connectors" or "new connectors" are not right. Something is seriously wrong with their dimensions or something as they fit too tight. As 3gengames said try playing the games without pushing the cartridge down at all and it might work. <br /><br />I've heard the better thing to do is to refurbish a Nintendo made connector. You can either try cleaning them or I've heard you can remove the pins from them and put in new ones.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Sat May 21, 2011 8:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
