<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7769&amp;p=78420#p78420"><![CDATA[
The most drastic method (but apparently working) I have ever heard of was used in this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YDGR2MiCyYs" class="postlink">video</a>.<br />The guy took the cartridge connector from a game genie and basicly built a top-loading NES out of a Toaster.<br />The other drastic method would be to install an AV-Mod to your top-loader.<br /><br />I'm not an expert with this, but it seems that both methods require you to do a lot of soldering...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4824">Grumskiz</a> — Sat May 21, 2011 6:38 am</p><hr />
